Former Senate President and presidential aspirant on the platform of the Peoples Democratic Party (PDP), Senator Anyim Pius Anyim, has assured that he will eliminate mutual suspicion, ensure unity and inspire patriotism if voted as president. Anyim gave the assurance in Ibadan while addressing all the South-West PDP delegates. He described the South-West as the brainbox of the nation and promised to partner with the zone on restructuring. The presidential aspirant told the delegates and party leaders that he is running for the presidency to reposition the country on the path of growth, peace and prosperity. Meanwhile, Oyo State Governor Seyi Makinde, who hosted Anyim at Government House, said he was pleased with the quality of aspirants that have emerged in the PDP for the 2023 presidential election. He said Anyimâ€™s experience as Senate President, Secretary to the Government of the Federation (SGF) and experienced lawyer stands him out.